This is For: 
Kali Linux (VirtualBox)
TryHackMe VPN
OpenVPN CLI method

STEP 1 — Start Kali Linux

Boot your Kali VM in VirtualBox.
Wait until desktop loads fully.

STEP 2 — Download VPN File (Inside Kali)

Open Firefox in Kali
Go to: https://tryhackme.com/access 
Select region: EU Ireland (any region works)

Click Download VPN
The file will download as something like: eu-west-1-{yourusername}-regular.ovpn
It saves to: /home/kali/Downloads

Open terminal in Kali.
Go to Downloads folder:  $ cd ~/Downloads

Check file exists: $ ls
You should see: eu-west-1-{yourusername}-regular.ovpn  (The Same file as downloaded)

Check if OpenVPN is Installed: $ openvpn --version
If its not installed: $ sudo apt update
                      $ sudo apt install openvpn -y

Connect to TryHackMe VPN: $ sudo openvpn eu-west-1-{yourusername}-regular.ovpn

STEP 6 — Confirm Connection
If successful, you will see:     Initialization Sequence Completed
                            
 Important Note: The terminal will NOT return to prompt
                 This is normal
                 Leave this terminal open
                 That means VPN is active.

Step 7 - Verify VPN Interface
Open a NEW terminal window.
Run: $ ip a
You should see: tun0
If tun0 exists → VPN connected successfully.

You are fully connected.
                                                            
